orian" era="ce" normal="1843/1843">1843</unitdate><container id="aspace_7d9315ce0c47e06ee579bc18c5ad1588" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_94874772cc31f4207a864934eda87fef" parent="aspace_7d9315ce0c47e06ee579bc18c5ad1588" type="folder">17</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_62940ac2599d23a370b4b8062e2b46d4" level="item"><did><unittitle>Tompkins County Election Returns, Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848 . Folder contains returns for various town, county, state, and federal elections held during this period. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>Ithaca Journal</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1836-11-30/1848-11-22" type="inclusive">Nov. 30, 1836-Nov. 22, 1848</unitdate><container id="aspace_6e2af45808ebf919888b9eec86a4dc0a" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_bb2bb9fb62a7b17f03305e147cbaf6cf" parent="aspace_6e2af45808ebf919888b9eec86a4dc0a" type="folder">18</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_8a7f96942566fca8837cb11c0479e48f" level="item"><did><unittitle>Articles on slavery, abolition, and colonization, Apr. 5, 1837-Apr. 18, 1838. Folder contains assorted articles on the issues surrounding slavery. Articles from <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title> and <title>The Ithaca Journal and Herald</title>.</unittitle><container id="aspace_2984502a7b25a6d4c4d94be0abf3ad56" label="Mixed Materials [31924064940921]" type="box">1</container><container id="aspace_0f473808e287e6cdba6e5650967bb34a" parent="aspace_2984502a7b25a6d4c4d94be0abf3ad56" type="folder">19</container></did></c01><c01 id="aspace_1c38f12fd9778ac3db661a741f138526" level="item"><did><unittitle>Residents of Tompkins County call meeting to discuss fiscal problems they believe caused by politicians in Albany. Article appears in May 7, 1834 <title>Ithaca Daily Chronicle</title>.</unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" normal="1834-05-07/1834-05-